text:
I'm very, very curious about the game against Germany tonight.

 We are in a very good form, we performed well in all our last Euro qualifier games, so we are coming to this game fully confident.

 But I wonder about the German team. With their abysmal performances those last few months reaching an all-time low this week-end against Japan + the Flick's sacking, I wonder if we could get a surprising match..

 I know everyone predicts a massacre like 7-0 for France, but I'm not so sure about it for a few reasons:

 - Firstly, it's a friendly so there is less incentive for our players to put on a show;
 - Secondly, we rarely score a lot of goals in our matches, even against very weak opponents;
 - Thirdly, Deschamps will probably not play our best starting XI since they already played a few days ago. I would not be surprised to see more of a B team with some A players here and there;
 - Fourthly, I really wonder if the German players could not rebound tonight against us. They reached an all-time low this week-end after months (years even) of downfall, but it's over with Flick now. They will have the remaining time before the Euro to prepare with a new coach, with new ideas, maybe find back their motivation etc., with the ultimate objective to perform well in front of their public during the Euro.. and tonight could be the turning point, the beginning of the climb back to their previous highs. Who could be better to bounce back and exceed all expectations than the vice-world champion themselves?

 I know this is a harebrained theory but, while everyone predicts a slaughter tonight, I would not be THAT surprised if the German players play well with a newfound motivation, and if we have a close and competitive game to watch.

 You're free to tell me that I'm insane.
